comment: A well-ordering can be constructed on a partitioned set by patching together well-orderings on each partition using a well-ordering on the partitions themselves. Similar to ~ fnwe but does not require the within-partition ordering to be globally well. (Contributed by Stefan O'Rear, 19-Jan-2015.)
